In this statement, President Obama announces that Ambassador Susan Rice has decided to remove her name from consideration for Secretary of State. He praises her as an exceptional public servant and highlights her accomplishments as Ambassador to the United Nations, including securing international support for sanctions against Iran and North Korea, protecting the people of Libya, and advocating for UN reform and human rights. The President expresses his gratitude for Susan's continued service as Ambassador to the UN and emphasizes her role as a key member of his cabinet and national security team. He expresses confidence in her ability to serve the country and states that he will continue to rely on her as an advisor and friend. The President also acknowledges the unfair attacks on Susan Rice and commends her for rising above the politics of the moment to prioritize national interests. He concludes by stating that the American people should be proud to have someone of her caliber and character representing the country.